  "body": "\r\n\r\n## 📝 Description\r\n\r\nThis PR introduces a new `TagsInput` component to Chakra UI, enabling users to enter and manage multiple values as tags. The component is built on top of Ark UI's tags-input primitive, providing a fully accessible and feature-rich tagging experience.\r\n\r\n## ⛳️ Current behavior (updates)\r\n\r\nChakra UI did not have a native component for managing multiple values as tags. Users had to build custom solutions or use third-party libraries.\r\n\r\n## 🚀 New behavior\r\n\r\n- **New `TagsInput` component** with the following parts:\r\n  - `TagsInput.Root` / `TagsInput.RootProvider` - Root container\r\n  - `TagsInput.Label` - Label for the input\r\n  - `TagsInput.Control` - Control wrapper for tags and input\r\n  - `TagsInput.Input` - Text input for adding new tags\r\n  - `TagsInput.Item` - Individual tag item\r\n  - `TagsInput.ItemText` - Text content of a tag\r\n  - `TagsInput.ItemInput` - Input for inline tag editing\r\n  - `TagsInput.ItemPreview` - Preview state of a tag\r\n  - `TagsInput.ItemDeleteTrigger` - Button to remove individual tags\r\n  - `TagsInput.ClearTrigger` - Button to clear all tags\r\n  - `TagsInput.HiddenInput` - Hidden input for form submission\r\n  - `TagsInput.Context` / `TagsInput.ItemContext` - Context consumers\r\n\r\n- **Theme recipe** (`tagsInput`) with:\r\n  - Sizes: `sm`, `md`, `lg`\r\n  - Variants: `outline`, `filled`, `flushed`\r\n\r\n- **UI Composition** (`tags-input.tsx`) providing:\r\n  - Pre-styled `TagsInputControl` with optional `clearable` prop\r\n  - Pre-styled `TagsInputItem` with integrated delete button\r\n  - Accessible `CloseButton` components with proper ARIA labels\r\n  - Convenient re-exports of all base components\r\n\r\n- **Documentation**:\r\n  - New documentation page with usage examples\r\n  - Storybook stories for visual testing\r\n\r\n- **Features**:\r\n  - Add tags by typing and pressing Enter or comma\r\n  - Remove individual tags with delete button or keyboard\r\n  - Clear all tags with clear button (when enabled)\r\n  - Inline tag editing (via `ItemInput` and `ItemPreview`)\r\n  - Full keyboard navigation support\r\n  - Form integration with hidden input\r\n  - Validation support with `onInvalid` callback\r\n\r\n## 💣 Is this a breaking change (Yes/No):\r\n\r\nNo\r\n\r\n## 📝 Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Component is marked as `beta` in documentation\r\n- Built on Ark UI's `@ark-ui/react/tags-input` primitive\r\n- Follows Chakra UI's composition patterns and theming system\r\n- Includes proper TypeScript types for all exported components\r\n- Accessible by default with proper ARIA attributes",
